sure this is the correct wrapping? 
https://cbea.ms/git-commit/
Wrap the body at 72 characters
For an internalError I think we should be BMCWEB_LOG_ERROR level. I know we aren't consistent here, but I think LOG_ERROR makes the most sense

It looks like - the only first serviceName for the object is used in 
```
    getFabricAdapterLocation(const std::shared_ptr<bmcweb::AsyncResp>& aResp,
                             const std::string& serviceName,
                             const std::string& fabricAdapterPath)
```
                             
Do all elements in object have the same "serviceName"?
serviceName is same, it is used in other places like powerSupply implementation.
Why do you need the getDbusObject call if you already have a GetSubTree call?
Removed call to getDbusObject and used serviceMap from GetSubTree.
